    <section class="page-hero">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label"><i class="fas fa-route"></i> Road Trip</span>
            <h1>EV Road Trip Planning Guide in India</h1>
            <p>Prepare longer journeys with the right charger stops, range planning, and route confidence for EV travel.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <div class="container container--narrow">
            <div class="card reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
                <h2>Plan your charging stops</h2>
                <p>For long EV trips, plan charging stops every 120-150 km. Use a mix of DC fast chargers and reliable city chargers to keep your journey smooth.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
                <h2>Use an app to map the route</h2>
                <p>ChargeKr helps you build a route with available chargers along the way. Choose stops with confirmed availability, especially on highways and in smaller towns.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
                <h2>Charge smart, not full</h2>
                <p>For road trips, charging from 20-80% is faster than charging to 100%. This saves time and keeps your trip moving without long waits at a charger.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
                <h2>Keep a buffer</h2>
                <p>Always leave a range buffer for detours and traffic. In India, that extra margin reduces stress and makes it easier to adapt if a charger is temporarily unavailable.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="text-center" style="margin-top:24px;">
                <a href="index.html#download" class="btn btn--primary">Download ChargeKr to plan your EV road trip →</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

